Vitae XII caesarium (Lives of the twelve caesars), fragment and Book of Hours leaf

Free Library of Philadelphia, Lewis E 195. Italy France, 16th century; 15th century. This manuscript is a fragment containing Suetonius' Lives of the Twelve Caesars, breaking off in the middle of the Life of Julius Caesar.
